<h3>Remarks:</h3>
<blockquote>
<em>2009-Jan-15 10:40:30 by gquinn:</em> <br>

This applies to suspending a family as well.

<p><hr>
<em>2012-May-18 08:31:05 by bbockelm:</em> <br>

Closing this ticket, as <span class="ticket"><a href="tktview?tn=1831" class="resolved"
title="Take advantage of cgroups-based capabilities on new Linux platforms"
>#1831</a></span> takes care of this in a generic, non-race-prone way.

<p>If people want better killing semantics, they should enable cgroups.</blockquote>
